	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 26th 3:47 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The skills at lvl 10 you need to be working on is fairly simple. All of them. As you have just turned 9 and got spells (congratz by the way) make sure that you train all 5 of the spell skills. Then buy your spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;The easiest way to train these, if you can, is on yourself. Just cast the lowest mana costing spell on yourself over and over to train that skill.   Easiest I found for lvl 9 and 15 to train them are :-<br><br>Divination - Sence Animals (lvl 15)<br>Abjuration - Inner Fire (level 9)<br>Alteration - Minor Healing (level 9, no need to train this seperatly as you will use this all the time)<br>Conjuration - Sicken (lvl 15. If you can get to one try this on a Nexus Scion. just stand a bit back, target the Scion and cast this over and over on them)<br>Evocation - Blast of Frost (lvl 15. Same as Conjuration)<br><br>The Scions never attacked me when I did this, so you should be ok, just try it once on the easiest to get to, and if it is different (ie you die) Im sorry, and please let me know.<br><br>Keep your weapon skills all trained (except maybe for 2HB, no one ever seems to use that). So when money allows buy a cheap but low delay weapon to train your skil, (Hand to hand(ALWAYS have this trained to the full), 1hb and piercing).<br><br>But the mostimportant is to PLAY your class, learn by your mistakes, and have fun.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Jan 26 03:21:05 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
