	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 13th 9:44 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Throwing weapons stink.&nbsp;&nbsp;That is just a plain truth of life in EQ.  Forged throwing weapons are slightly better than store bought.  You only need a smithing skill of 60 to trivial all the forged throwing weapons.  I like forged throwing axes. Better range, slightly better damage, and stackable where as store bought throwing axes are not.  They cost about 5gp each to make.<br><br>Rogues get critical hits and deadly strike with thrown weapons.  BL's don't.  Don't get too upset. Crits and deadly strike do about 30 pts with a shuriken and are rare. So, most rogues I know take up archery. The damage is more consistant.<br><br>If you are really ambitious and flush with cash get your smithing up to 115 which is the trivial for Velium Forged Throwing weapons.  They proc Velium Shards for an extra 12 pts of damage (unless its resisted). <br><br>In Echo Caverns some of the mobs drop claws that are throwing weapons. Damage is ok (for a throwing weapon) and range is good.  But you can sell them to a vendor for up to 3pp each so why throw them away?<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
