	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;   As a LVL 58 Bst I've spent most of my time soloing. What I have found is that there are 2 types of styles of play that work well for a Bl. The type I play is partial tank to my pet I started with 20 wis but all my gear is prety much designed for a monk. I have high str dex and agi with wis comming in 4th. The most important stat on  my gear is agi because as a BL I can buff all other melee stats for an additional 50+ per stat. I just melee the mob till it reaches about 60% health then set back and regen while my pet finishes the scraps. This method usually only requires that I cast 1 heal on my pet and proves very efficiant. There are many ways to extend a Bl mana pool using regen, increasing spell duration and decrease spell cast cost and make a small mana pool last longer.<br> The other type  of Bl  is the pet cleric. This is a simple method to play as you just keep your pet healed while it does all the fighting. It possible for a BL to solo tougher mobs with this method provided they have a significant mana pool to dive into. A combinaytion of Dot's nukes and heals alloy this class to solo very tough mobs even white cons at my lvl. The only downfall is this class will have more down time due to the large mana pool and the amount of mana used per kill.<br>   <br>     Ketath 58th vah shir Bst <br>        Tribunal server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
