	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 6th 10:12 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.49]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>STR is good since you get a damage bonus at higher levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;STA is good since it gives more HP. It also determines how well you fight when you are exhausted (your yellow fatigue bar is empty). WIS is good since you get more mana.  Now that we can chain summon warders more mana is a good thing.  Also, at higher levels BL's get some nice group buffs.  So, again, more mana is good.  DEX helps your offensive skills climb faster (good until the skill is max'd for you level).  It also helps slightly with increasing how often a weapon's special effects (procs) go off (assuming your weapon has one).  Personally, I find them unreliable.  AGI helps increase the rate at which your defensive skills climb. It also helps a little with your AC rating.<br><br>So, if you dump your points in WIS you won't be too badly off. Barbarians have a naturally high STR and STA to begin with that are adequate and can get boosted with gear.<br><br>I happen to be in the &quot;AC first, HP 2nd, Mana 3rd&quot;, then everything else school of thought.  There are others who feel differently. So, I took my Ogre BL's WIS to 100 to start. Now I just get gear that fits my thinking.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
