	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 7th 8:47 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you give your pet a weapon it will use it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Pets, to my knowledge, have equal skill with any weapon.  So the damage rating of the weapon will make a difference.  But it is possible that warders, unlike other pets, do better with HtoH weapons since that is the combat mode of choice for them; whereas other pets (necro, chanter, and magician) actually do improve using weapons provided that weapon has better damage/delay ratio than their own HtoH skill.<br><br>Also keep in mind that a weapon may hit for less damage but more often. So, the total damage per minute might be higher even though each individual hit is less.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
