	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104788520980419><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=15&mid=104788520980419>RE: Pet + Weap?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=15&mid=104788520980419#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93315><span id=Scholar>Jeroo</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>51 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 17th 2:47 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, uh, no.<br><br>Delay on a weapon means nothing for pets anymore.&nbsp;&nbsp;Long ago, it used to be important, but now all pets use a delay of 31, no matter what the weapon given to them.  Necros are still crying over this change.<br><br>Damage on a weapon only means anything if you give a pet a weapon that does more damage than what it does with bare fists.  Give a magician's lvl 4 pet a rusty scythe, and it will do more damage.  Give a level 12 pet that scythe, and you won't see any more damage than if it didn't have it.<br><br>What does matter is procs.  High level magician summoned weapons (blade of walnan, fist of ixiblat, blade of the kedge, etc.) all do extra damage via the procs of the weapon.<br><br>All pets, save warders, have equal skill with any weapon.  Warders have more skill with H2H weapons than anything else.  Give a high level BL pet a sword, and you're crippling its damage output, even with the procs.  Give it Fists instead.<br>&nbsp;<br>--<br>Jeroo Ashstaff</td></tr>
